    "Since our preferences are not inherently orthogonal, we select two dimensions with the least collinearity, which are culture and age (see correlation analysis in Figure E.1 in Appendix E).",
    "We vary the steering strength for each dimension uniformly and measure the effect of each preference separately.",
    "The steering vector is applied as a weighed combination of the individual preference vectors.With compounded steering, the main concern is that the effects will deteriorate.",
